	<td><p>Biryani is a celebrated, aromatic rice dish from the Indian subcontinent, traditionally featuring long-grain basmati rice layered with marinated meat (or vegetables) and cooked using the dum method—steaming over a slow fire.</p></td>
	<td><p>Making cheesecake involves creating a creamy, cheese-based filling (usually cream cheese, sugar, and eggs) poured over a crust—commonly graham cracker—and baking it slowly, often in a water bath to prevent cracks.</p></td>
	<td><p>Chicken Kadai (or Karahi) is a popular, high-heat North Indian/Pakistani stir-fry dish, defined by cooking bone-in chicken in a traditional wok (karahi) with tomatoes, ginger-garlic paste, and a unique, freshly ground masala (coriander, cumin, chilies).</p></td>
 </tr>
