 <article>
 <h2>How to make Brownie</h2>
 <ul><h3>Ingredients List (Standard Recipe):</h3>
	<li><strong>Fat</strong>: 1/2 cup (115g) unsalted butter</li>
	<li><strong>Chocolate</strong>: 1 cup semi-sweet chips or chopped dark chocolate</li>
	<li><strong>Sugar</strong>: 1 cup granulated or brown sugar (or a mix)</li>
	<li><strong>Eggs</strong>: 2 large eggs</li>
	<li><strong>Flavoring</strong>: 1 tsp vanilla extract</li>
	<li><strong>Dry</strong>: 1/2 cup all-purpose flour, 1/4 cup cocoa powder (optional), 1/4 tsp salt</li>
 </ul>
 
 <ol><h3>Key Steps and Tips for Success:</h3>
	<li><strong>Preparation</strong>: Preheat oven to \(350^{\circ }\text{F}\) (\(175^{\circ }\text{C}\)) or \(180^{\circ }\text{C}\) and line an 8x8 inch metal baking pan with parchment paper for easy removal.</li>
	<li><strong>Melting</strong>: Melt butter and dark chocolate/cocoa powder together in a saucepan or microwave for a smooth, rich base.</li>
	<li><strong>Mixing</strong>: Whisk the eggs and sugar thoroughly until fluffy before adding to the chocolate mixture; this helps create a crackly top.</li>
	<li><strong>Texture Control</strong>: For fudgy brownies, do not overbake. Use a toothpick to check for moist crumbs, not a dry stick, at around 25-30 minutes.</li>
 </ol>
 
